---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/docs.astro';
const rawBase = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const base = rawBase.endsWith('/') ? rawBase : rawBase + '/';
---
<DocsLayout title="Installation" current="Installation">

<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">Installation</h1>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">Clawsewitz runs as a standalone CLI in any terminal. It's also available as a Claude Code plugin.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="npm">npm (recommended)</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Install globally with npm — requires Node.js 20.19 or later:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">npm install -g clawsewitz</code>
</div>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Then run from any directory:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto flex flex-col gap-1">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">clawsewitz</code>
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-muted"># or with a brief:</code>
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">clawsewitz "Acme — subscriber decline, need turnaround"</code>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="curl">One-line installer</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">On macOS or Linux, install without npm:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">curl -fsSL https://robertsinke.github.io/clawsewitz/install | bash</code>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="plugin">Claude Code plugin</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">If you prefer to use clawsewitz inside Claude Code instead of as a standalone CLI:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">curl -fsSL https://robertsinke.github.io/clawsewitz/install-plugin | bash</code>
</div>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">This installs clawsewitz as a Claude Code plugin with slash commands (<code class="font-mono text-[13px] bg-prussian-tint px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">/clawsewitz</code>, <code class="font-mono text-[13px] bg-prussian-tint px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">/cw-decompose</code>, etc.) and subagent delegation. Same strategy content, different runtime.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="verify">Verifying the installation</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Check that everything is working:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto flex flex-col gap-1">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">clawsewitz --version</code>
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-muted"># 1.0.0</code>
</div>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto flex flex-col gap-1">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">clawsewitz doctor</code>
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-muted"># ✓ Pi runtime found</code>
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-muted"># ✓ Extension found</code>
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-muted"># ✓ Prompt templates found</code>
</div>
<p class="text-text-secondary">If all checks pass, you're ready. See the <a href={`${base}docs/quickstart`} class="text-prussian underline underline-offset-2">Quick Start</a> guide to run your first engagement.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="updating">Updating</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Update via npm:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">npm update -g clawsewitz</code>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="uninstalling">Uninstalling</h2>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">npm uninstall -g clawsewitz</code>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="skills-only">Skills-only bundle</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">If you only want the strategy skills and framework library without agents or workflows:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">curl -fsSL https://robertsinke.github.io/clawsewitz/install-skills | bash</code>
</div>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">This installs only the <code class="font-mono text-[13px] bg-prussian-tint px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">skills/</code> and <code class="font-mono text-[13px] bg-prussian-tint px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">references/</code> directories. No agents, no slash commands, no enforcement. Use when you want the 70 frameworks and reference material inside your own orchestration.</p>

</DocsLayout>
